==Standard dialogue==
===Before starting [[Ratcatchers]]===
* '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Who are you, and what do you want?
* '''Player:''' My name is Dazaator, and I have a couple of questions for you.
* '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' No.
* '''Player:''' What?
* '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' I don't know you, therefore I will not answer any questions. Now be gone from here, you're drawing attention.
* '''Player:''' As if those clothes you're wearing wouldn't do that already.
* {{tact|end}}

===Trying to go down the nearby ladder into the Rat Pits===
* '''Player:''' I can't see the bottom of the ladder. I think I'll leave it be, for now.
* {{tact|end}}

===After completing [[Ratcatchers]]===
* '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Ah, [player name]. Back for more intonation?
* {{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me where I can find...}}
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Grimesquit and Phingspet}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me where I can find Phingspet and Grimesquit?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' They live in the sewers below Varrock. 
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Please don't say hello from me.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Hooknosed Jack}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me where I can find Hooknosed Jack?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' He hangs around in a rather unfashionable part of Varrock. He likes a good scrap, does Jack.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Smokin' Joe}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me where I can find Smokin' Joe?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' If the old rascal's lungs haven't given up yet, you should find him in Keldagrim.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|The Face}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me where I might find 'The Face'?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Port Sarim is your best bet.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{topt|Felkrash}}
*** '''Player:''' Can you tell me where I might find Felkrash?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' The Boss? 
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' You'll find her in Port Sarim, probably in the Rat Pits there.
*** '''Player:''' She's your boss?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Well, sort of. She's the unofficial leader of the Ratcatchers.
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Nobody elected her or anything.
*** '''Player:''' Got it. She's the boss.
*** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|Can you tell me more about the Rat Pits?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you tell me more about the pits?
** {{tcond|If the player does not have the Rat Pits manual:}}
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Here take this, you might find it useful.
*** {{tbox|pic=Book (Ratpits) detail.png|You are handed the rat pits manual.}}
*** {{tact|continue}}
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' What do you want to know?
** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
** {{topt|Do you have any pointers for me and my cat?}}
*** '''Player:''' Do you have any pointers for me and my cat?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' You should wear an Amulet of Catspeak. It will allow you to organise tactics with your cat.
*** '''Player:''' What would be the best tactic to adopt then?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Well, that depends on your outlook, whether you're ready to risk your cat's life or not and how defensive or aggressive you want your cat to be.
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|I will not risk my cat's life.}}
**** '''Player:''' I will not risk my cat's life.
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Well if that's the case then you're left with two choices.
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' You can adopt an ultra defensive strategy, which increases your cat's hitpoints and defence but causes it to flee sooner. 
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Or you can adopt a less defensive strategy, which will allow your cat to stay in the pit for longer.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|I think I would adopt an ultra defensive strategy.}}
***** '''Player:''' I think I would adopt a very defensive strategy{{sic}}
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In that case you should tell your cat: 'Just take care of yourself, cat.'
***** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Do you have any other questions about the pits?
***** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
***** {{topt|I'd like to ask you...}}
****** {{tact|initial}}
***** {{topt|No thanks}}
****** '''Player:''' No thanks.
****** {{tact|end}}
**** {{topt|I think I would adopt a less defensive strategy.}}
***** '''Player:''' I think I would adopt a less defensive strategy.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In that case you should tell your cat: 'Stay in for as long as you can.'
***** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Do you have any other questions about the pits?
***** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
***** {{topt|I'd like to ask you...}}
****** {{tact|above}}
***** {{topt|No thanks}}
****** {{tact|above}}
*** {{topt|I am willing to risk my cat if it improves my chances.}}
**** '''Player:''' I am willing to risk my cat, if it increases my chances of victory.
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In that case you are left with two choices.
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' You could go for all out attack which will boost your cat's attack and strength, but weaken it.
**** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Or, go for a less aggressive stance, which will increase your cat's strength and attack to a lesser degree, but carries no defensive penalties.
**** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
**** {{topt|I think I would adopt a very aggressive strategy.}}
***** '''Player:''' I think I would adopt a very aggressive strategy.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In that case you should tell your cat: 'Go berserk!'
***** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Do you have any other questions about the pits?
***** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
***** {{topt|I'd like to ask you...}}
****** {{tact|above}}
***** {{topt|No thanks}}
****** {{tact|above}}
**** {{topt|I think I would adopt a less aggressive strategy.}}
***** '''Player:''' I think I would adopt a less aggressive strategy.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In that case you should tell your cat: 'No guts, no glory!'
***** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help.
***** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Do you have any other questions about the pits?
***** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
***** {{topt|I'd like to ask you...}}
****** {{tact|above}}
***** {{topt|No thanks}}
****** {{tact|above}}
** {{topt|What benefits does my cat get from training in the pits?}}
*** '''Player:''' What benefits does my cat get from training in the pits?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' It depends on what kind of cat you have.
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' In the Ardougne pits, your kitten will grow up faster whether it wins or loses.
*** '''Player:''' What if it wins then?
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' It will gain more experience, it'll be happier, and it'll be fed, too.
*** '''Player:''' Thanks for your help.
*** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Do you have any other questions about the pits?
*** {{tselect|Select an Option}}
*** {{topt|I'd like to ask you...}}
**** {{tact|above}}
*** {{topt|No thanks}}
**** {{tact|above}}
* {{topt|Can you show me to the Rat Pits?}}
** '''Player:''' Can you show me to the Rat Pits?
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' See that ladder there? That's the way in.
** '''Player:''' Thanks.
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Good luck!
** {{tact|end}}
* {{topt|How do you spell your name again?}}
** '''Player:''' How do you spell your name again?
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:'''  J-I-M-M-Y D-A-Z-Z-L-E-R. 
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:'''  Why?
** '''Player:''' Ever thought about putting a '1' in it?
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Why on Gielinor would I do that?
** '''Player:''' Might add a bit of pizzazz, that's all.
** '''Jimmy Dazzler:''' Pizzazz, you say? I'll think about it.
** {{tact|end}}

